fr.jgetmove.jgetmove.debug

Class Debug

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.jgetmove.jgetmove.debug.Debug

  • public final class Debug
extends java.lang.Object
    Class used to display Logs.

    Has different display statuses :

    • DEBUG
    • INFO
    • WARNING : displays all the text in orange
    • ERROR : displays all the text in red

    note: only DEBUG is hidden if enable() is not used. all the others statuses are displayed in the System.out

    note: if PrettyPrint is implemented by the object, it will use PrettyPrint.toPrettyString() instead of Object.toString()

    Since:
    0.2.0
    See Also:
    enable(), disable(), print(Object, int), print(PrettyPrint, int), print(String, Object, int), print(String, PrettyPrint, int), println(Object, int), println(PrettyPrint, int), (Object, int), println(String, PrettyPrint, int), displayTitle(), printTitle(String, int), stack(char), stack(char, String), unstack(), indent(String), now()
